=title> People who think they can handle PoP but have no clue.</span><hr size=1> Plane of Nightmares - is like rolling craps when you zone in. Half the time some idiot who was quadkiting trained the zonein/graveyard. <br>
<br>
Plane of Innovation - Karnor's has nothing on the trains people make here. Here's a hint people...Those doors along the path...they are safe places to make camps. The path and the zone in are not. If you camp the path, other groups will have to move through you to get to a real camp. Eventually someone will try to pull through another group and fail or piss somebody off. My best laugh in PoP to date was when one group who was camping a spot in the path got territorial on our group that was moving through and proceeded to pull large numbers of mobs through our group. The end result was our group got seven or eight rapid exps messages and their group got mostly wiped out. Heres another hint. The way to move past a group in the paths of PoI is to move as a group and play leapfrog with the other group. Pulling through other groups doesnt always work. <br>
<br>
Plane of Justice - Training the zone is STUPID...the zone out is soo much closer to anywhere you found a mob.<br>
<br>
Talking to NPC's...If someone is chatting with an event starting NPC, wait till they are finished before talking to see what the NPC had to say. Some events can get bugged if the NPC is hailed at the wrong time by the wrong person.<br>
<br>
Trails...If its not a trial with virtual copies, wait for the people ahead of you to finish, clean up and get out before you head in. Its really in everyones interest to be patient as having the extra people in there will usually just cause it to be bugged for everyone.<br>
<br>
