<br>
I'd have to say I've been trained more since I bought PoP than I have been in my entire 2 and a half years playing this game. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46329"><img src="http://www.thepalecourt.com/signaturevara.jpg"><BR>61 Iksar Grandmaster<a> Celestial Fist - Whistling Fist of Thule </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showUserPublicProfile?gid=razerzedgeemarr>RazerZedgeEmarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/30/02 6:06:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3765.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who think they can handle PoP but have no clue.</span><hr size=1> If you zone into PoN, you should move up the hillside. If you die and get rezzed at the graveyard, loot your corpse and move up the hillside.<br>
<br>
I've been in exp groups, hanging out at the graveyard waiting on people, and I suggest that we move up the wall. 5 out of 6 people move up the wall, and sit down. The 6th person sits in the graveyard, gets trained, and has to zone. He comes back in, sits down in GY again, gets trained again, and has to zone again. Then he asks where we are, and we tell him we're sitting safe on the wall, watching him get trained over and over, and he finally comes and joins us :P<br>
<br>
Plane of Innovation is harder, not much room at zone in, but it's usually a good idea to park yourself across the opening from the portal so you're as far from trained mobs as possible. If you sit right beside the portal, you'll get trained. Just like people in UP who think that camping the zone in is safer than any camps to the left or right of the tunnel. They get trained a lot more than I ever did in the right safe valley(one time that I remember), but they never leave cause they want to be right there a few feet from the zone, just in case. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138154"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tbaytel.net/scaryf/images/everquest/razeratof.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalamarndarkgem>Dalamarn Darkgem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 645<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/30/02 9:32:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3765.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who think they can handle PoP but have no clue.</span><hr size=1> The accidental training is bad enough.  The intentional training in PoN is as bad as the villian in a bad &quot;b&quot; movie.  People get super territorial and train people that picked up an add as they ran past their camp (up on the wall).  Some people are just asses and I sat invis and watched someone run a train through graveyard about every 5 minutes to lose mobs on the people just zoning in.<br>
<br>
Then there're the quadding druids and wizzies who run out of mana with a group of mobs still up and have to make a mad dash to zoneout (which is the same as zone in for all practical purposes).  I think all the DL/KC idiots just moved to PoN. <p>&lt;a href=&quot;http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;<br>
