<br>
When we finally got around there and started killing stuff, someone managed to train spiders and banshee's on us. since we figured that noone would be camping the zone out on the lower level, we decided to train out just to save some time. I shouted 3 times that we were training that zone out, said that if anyone was there they should move away, but when the SK in group got near, he saw a group hanging out there, and hit Feign Death. soon as he hit the ground the mobs on him turned on me, and since I was behind him and in the middle of all the mobs they stunned and mauled me to death.<br>
<br>
would be nice if zones with more than 2 exit points had at least one that didn't have people camping beside it :P<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, I found a way up the ledge today in nightmare. Below the werewoofs and north a tad, right behind the slurghiblarghs, I found that I could walk up the cliff. Being a shorty probably had everything to do with this, and if that's so, haffers rule! other classes with lev should be able to do the same thing. the fishpeeps don't see invis either.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138154"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tbaytel.net/scaryf/images/everquest/razeratof.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coajikdeloloth>Coajik Deloloth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/31/02 5:26:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3765.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PoI trains</span><hr size=1> So far I have only taken the time to travel to PoD and PoI....PoD was alright..for the most part..the zone in and zone out were so close..that even if someone was lame enough to try to pull over the slime water you could likely escape...<br>
<br>
     PoI was a different matter altogether...our &quot;group&quot; happened to decided to check it out the same night that another group was up there raiding. We zoned in apparently right after the raid had pulled some high level MoB to the zone in...the creature..(I wish I could remember the name) wiped out the entire raid then went ahead and killed all those in our group who didn't have Harmshield/Divine Aura....immediately following that it corpse camped the raid for another hour or so...pleasant...seems like perhaps zone in is not a good place to set up camp there..even for a large raid.<br>
<br>
